sections.Biography:
===Background===
{{Quote|Aegon's own son, Maegor the Cruel, was killed by the very Iron Throne his father had forged... if you believe the tales. If you don't, then perhaps 'the Cruel' is not a wise name for a king to earn.|[[Varys]]|Histories &amp; Lore}}
[[File:Maegor.jpg|thumb|left|Maegor working with the [[Alchemists' Guild]].]]Maegor was a ruler in the [[House Targaryen|Targaryen dynasty]]. He finished constructing theÂ [[Red Keep]]Â during his reign,&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Cripples, Bastards and Broken Things]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt; including [[Maegor's Holdfast]], which was named after him. The holdfast is the tower at the center of the [[Red Keep]] in [[King's Landing]].&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Blackwater]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

After the construction was finished, Maegor had all the workers and masons killed to protect its secrets.&lt;ref&gt;[[The Red Keep (Histories &amp; Lore)]]&lt;/ref&gt;

===[[Season 1]]===
While visiting the [[Great Hall (Red Keep)|Great Hall]] of the [[Red Keep]] and after being asked by [[Septa]] [[Mordane]], [[Sansa Stark]] mentions Maegor the Cruel had the Red Keep built.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Cripples, Bastards and Broken Things]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

===[[Season 2]]===
[[Hallyne]] mentions Maegor as an advocate of the [[Alchemists' Guild]] and a patron of their work on [[Wildfire|the Substance]].&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[The Ghost of Harrenhal]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;
